---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contribute"
  description="How to contribute sourced data and corrections."
>
  <section class="directory-hero py-14">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow">Contribute</p>
      <h1 class="section-title mt-3">Improve the archive with sources</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-archive card max-w-3xl p-6">
      <p>
        Contributions should include the exact record being changed, the
        proposed wording or data value, and at least one official or
        authoritative source. Do not add unsourced nationality, adviser,
        quotation, image, or prize-value data.
      </p>
      <p>
        Preferred sources are official award pages, institutional biographies,
        personal academic pages, peer-reviewed literature, mathematical
        societies, or trusted academic databases.
      </p>
      <p>
        For new award or laureate data, include completeness status and last
        verification date. Incomplete records are welcome when clearly labelled.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
